==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|wepen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|wǣpen||weapon, sword, arms}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*wēpną||weapon}}, of unknown origin, possibly from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*wēbnom}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|wapyn|lang=sco}}, {{term|wappen||weapon|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|wapen||weapon|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|wapen||weapon|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|wapen||weapon|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Waffe||weapon|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|vapen||weapon|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|vopn||weapon|lang=is}}.

